@startuml TransCredit_Cancellation_Process
title TransCredit Cancellation Processing (As Is)

start

:Receive Cancellation Request;
note right
  Cancellations occur when:
  - Loan paid off early
  - Loan charged off
  - Loan refinanced
  - Life claim paid (disability cancelled)
  Received via email or monthly report
end note

:Find Certificate in System;
note right
  System automatically finds last certificate
  by agent number and pre-fills information
  Staff verifies correct certificate
end note

:Enter Cancel Date;
note right
  Staff enters cancellation date
  provided by bank/agent
end note

:Calculate Premium Refund;
note right
  System automatically calculates
  premium refund based on cancellation date
  Uses refund method (pro-rata or Rule 78)
end note

:Enter Bank Refund Amount;
note right
  Staff enters refund amount
  provided by bank
end note

:Tolerance Check;
note right
  System checks if bank amount
  is within tolerance
  - Within tolerance: Accept
  - Out of tolerance: Flag as error
end note

if (Within tolerance?) then (yes)
  :Accept Cancellation;
  note right
    Cancellation saved
    Transaction Type = 20 (Cancellation)
    Appears in C-List report
  end note
else (no)
  :Flag as Error;
  note right
    Error appears in error list
    Shows calculated vs bank amount
    Staff contacts agent to resolve
  end note
endif

:Update C-List Report;
note right
  Cancellation transaction added
  to Customer List report
  Shows refund amount and date
end note

:Complete Cancellation Processing;

stop

@enduml

